  "prompt": "Which phone should I buy under INR 15K?",
  "response": "When looking for a smartphone under INR 15,000, you have several good options that offer a balance between performance, features, and affordability. Here are some top recommendations as of late 2023:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Realme Narzo 60x 5G**\n   - **Key Features**: \n     - **Display**: 6.72-inch FHD+ 120Hz display\n     - **Processor**: Dimensity 6100+ 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 50MP primary + 2MP depth\n     - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Smooth display, 5G support, good battery life.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 12,999.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Redmi 12 5G**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.79-inch FHD+ 90Hz display\n     - **Processor**: Snapdragon 4 Gen 2 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 50MP primary + 2MP depth\n     - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: 5G-ready, large display, decent performance.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 13,999.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Samsung Galaxy M14 5G**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.6-inch FHD+ 90Hz display\n     - **Processor**: Exynos 1330 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 50MP primary + 2MP macro + 2MP depth\n     - **Battery**: 6000mAh with 25W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Long battery life, reliable software updates, 5G support.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 13,990.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Infinix GT 10 Pro**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.67-inch FHD+ 120Hz AMOLED display\n     - **Processor**: Dimensity 8050 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 108MP primary + 2MP depth + 2MP macro\n     - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 45W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: AMOLED display, excellent camera, fast charging.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 14,999.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Motorola G54 5G**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.5-inch FHD+ 120Hz display\n     - **Processor**: Dimensity 7020 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 50MP primary + 8MP ultra-wide\n     - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Clean Android experience, stereo speakers, 5G support.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 14,999.\n\n---\n\n### **6. POCO M6 Pro 5G**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.79-inch FHD+ 90Hz display\n     - **Processor**: Dimensity 6100+ 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 50MP primary + 2MP depth\n     - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Good performance, 5G support, value for money.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 14,999.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Lava Agni 2 5G**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.78-inch FHD+ 120Hz AMOLED display\n     - **Processor**: Dimensity 7050 5G chipset\n     - **Camera**: 50MP primary + 8MP ultra-wide + 2MP macro + 2MP depth\n     - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 66W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: AMOLED display, premium design, fast charging.\n   - **Price**: Starts around INR 14,999.\n\n---\n\n### **Things to Consider**:\n1. **5G Support**: Ensure the phone is 5G ready for future-proofing.\n2. **Battery Life**: Look for phones with 5000mAh or higher capacity.\n3. **Display**: Choose a higher refresh rate (90Hz or 120Hz) for smoother visuals.\n4. **Camera**: Prioritize phones with good primary cameras if photography is important.\n5. **Brand Preference**: Consider after-sales service and software updates.\n\nLet me know if you need further details about any of these options!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
